The paper deals with learning with noisy labels, which is a common problem in machine learning. The proposed method is based on a Bayesian framework and involves dynamic label regression. The paper uses datasets such as CIFAR-10, CIFAR-100, Clothing1M, and WebVision17, which are commonly used in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
